      <section>
        <title>Apocalypse Now</title>
        <chapter>
          <paragraph>Despite central banks' monetary policy decisions, the global economy is going very bad. The situation is out of control: The world's public debt weights a lot on the economy, and the same is for inflation and money volatility. Central banks are worried about it, but what could they do for improving this situation? Maybe, their control is limited and they can’t predict everything.
