          <paragraph>Emergency liquidity Assistance (ELA) means institutions can receive central bank credit through emergency liquidity assistance. Greece central bank receives 59.5 billion euros, but this is not for free, in fact the interst is 1.55% instead of 0.05%.</paragraph>
